  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (residual-risk-unjustified variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: a known limitation exists in that non-Newtonian blood rheology effects at low shear rates were not incorporated into the model; this edge case is acknowledged but the assessment proceeds to Accepted without documenting why the residual risk associated with this limitation is acceptable for the COU.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-credibility",
